		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://jamesclear-com.uar9g7bv-liquidwebsites.com/?p=5305#comment-9435</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Great piece James!

Intermittent Fasting is something I&#039;ve been utilizing for years myself and it is working great. Having read many scientific journals on the topic recently, I&#039;m even more confident now, that IF is probably one of the best sustainable dieting approaches out there. Actually, I don&#039;t really want to call it a diet at all, but rather a lifestyle choice.

I&#039;ve even managed to hit the bodybuilding stage using IF, so yeah, it can be used  by anyone for sure. It may not be for everyone, but I think most people should try it out at-least once.

Personally I also tend to use the 16:8 pattern, but sometimes I change it up to as low as 12/12 or higher like 20:4. Recently I&#039;ve also gone more towards Brad Pilon&#039;s method, which is utilizing a roughly 24 hour fast 1-2x a week.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Great piece James!</p>
<p>Intermittent Fasting is something I&#8217;ve been utilizing for years myself and it is working great. Having read many scientific journals on the topic recently, I&#8217;m even more confident now, that IF is probably one of the best sustainable dieting approaches out there. Actually, I don&#8217;t really want to call it a diet at all, but rather a lifestyle choice.</p>
<p>I&#8217;ve even managed to hit the bodybuilding stage using IF, so yeah, it can be used  by anyone for sure. It may not be for everyone, but I think most people should try it out at-least once.</p>
<p>Personally I also tend to use the 16:8 pattern, but sometimes I change it up to as low as 12/12 or higher like 20:4. Recently I&#8217;ve also gone more towards Brad Pilon&#8217;s method, which is utilizing a roughly 24 hour fast 1-2x a week.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
